e same time and heat for 10 minutes (180°C).","Rest lamb loins for 5 minutes before carving. Smear some carrot and ginger purée across each plate, top with slices of lamb loin then place a warmed lamb patty (remove rings) to one side. Drizzle lamb loin with a little red wine jus. Serve with remaining jus, and wilted spinach if desired."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Slow Cooked Lamb Shoulder","content":["25 g vegetable oil","750 g lamb shoulder meat, boneless, diced","1 pinch fine sea salt","1 pinch ground black pepper","2 Tbsp cornflour","1 meat stock cube (for 0.5 l) (lamb)","500 g water","1 sprig fresh rosemary","1 garlic clove"]},{"title":"Red Wine Jus","content":["1 banana shallot, halved","1 garlic clove","1 small handful mixed fresh herbs, leaves only (approx. 5 g)","50 g salted butter","100 g port","150 g red wine","20 g balsamic vinegar","35 g dark brown sugar              (optional)","1 pinch fine sea salt, or to taste","1 pinch ground black pepper, or to taste"]},{"title":"Carrot and Ginger Purée","content":["30 g olive oil","500 g carrots, cut in 4 pieces","15 g fresh root ginger, peeled, cut in slices (2 mm)","100 g water","½ tsp fine sea salt","100 g butter, cut in pieces","ground black pepper, for seasoning"]},{"title":"Roasted Lamb Loin","content":["1 Tbsp vegetable oil","6 lamb loin (100-150 g each)","2 pinches fine sea salt, for seasoning","2 pinches ground black pepper, for seasoning","10 g butter, for basting","fresh spinach, wilted, for serving (optional)"]}],"id":"r130204","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-37FS1toT5bY\/XZQvPSwPlgI\/AAAAAAAAcbc\/fMIcv6V3zfIHKxwkchV-_7mHqSszFQc4ACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_DjFlQZf3OCB1AGIU.png","title":"Lamb Cooked Two Ways with Carrot and Ginger Purée and Red Wine Jus","publishedAt":"2016-12-12T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"35.3 g","fat":"45.7 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"21.3 g","calories":"2670 kJ \/ 638 kcal"},"usefulItems":"casserole dish, slotted spoon, fine sieve, saucepan, cling film, ba